Linkage FAIL

Simple Firefox Extension for alerting you when a page has some external elements which aren't linked properly.

Use when busting out simple HTML changes and you aren't using Firebug Net tab.

On / Off switch - Firefox > Tools > Add-ons > Extensions Enable / Disable

=== Build Script / Dev setup ===
This project uses code generated by the Extension Wizard at
http://ted.mielczarek.org/code/mozilla/extensionwiz/ .
http://kb.mozillazine.org/Getting_started_with_extension_development

Prod Builds:
You can build an XPI for installation by running the
build.sh script located in this folder.

Development you should do the following:
  1. edit profile-extensions/ozten@borkenLink to have the path to this directory
  2. Copy it into your Profile/extensions directory
  3. Restart Firefox.
  
  Now no builds are required, restart FF as needed.